1
00:00:39,415 --> 00:00:40,745
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,745 --> 00:00:42,175
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:43,315 --> 00:00:44,485
What if it were possible...

4
00:00:45,345 --> 00:00:48,115
to swap only the brain
without changing the face?

5
00:00:48,855 --> 00:00:49,885
By any chance,

6
00:00:50,855 --> 00:00:52,055
are you talking about you, Director?

7
00:00:54,695 --> 00:00:56,065
If it were possible,
who would I swap with?

8
00:00:57,495 --> 00:00:58,495
Momo.

9
00:00:59,665 --> 00:01:00,665
No way.

10
00:01:23,985 --> 00:01:25,825
Looks like we're the only guys here
on our own.

11
00:01:26,255 --> 00:01:27,555
I guess it's because of your job,

12
00:01:27,925 --> 00:01:29,765
but you're always so conscious
of what others think.

13
00:01:30,765 --> 00:01:32,095
- I think that's him.
- I'm telling you, it is.

14
00:01:32,335 --> 00:01:34,295
I think that woman
over there recognizes me.

15
00:01:34,295 --> 00:01:35,865
- Right?
- She must.

16
00:01:35,865 --> 00:01:37,005
A look like this is one of a kind.

17
00:01:39,205 --> 00:01:40,605
Doesn't anyone recognize you?

18
00:01:41,105 --> 00:01:43,445
Sometimes. The younger crowd, mostly.

19
00:01:43,675 --> 00:01:45,645
I can't even eat out with actors.

20
00:01:46,015 --> 00:01:48,115
They're always asking
for an autograph or a picture.

21
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:52,115
You win some, you lose some.
That's the price of fame.

22
00:01:52,915 --> 00:01:55,985
Didn't you always say
there's no such thing as a free lunch?

23
00:01:56,425 --> 00:01:57,655
Yesterday, Ju Shin said...

24
00:01:58,355 --> 00:02:00,595
you and Reporter Geum looked
like a couple.

25
00:02:02,295 --> 00:02:04,925
- And?
- I told him he's way off.

26
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,235
You two must have been pretty cozy
for him to say that.

27
00:02:08,295 --> 00:02:09,405
What are you talking about?

28
00:02:10,435 --> 00:02:12,905
You two are like brother and sister,
while she keeps me at arm's length.

29
00:02:20,915 --> 00:02:21,915
Hey.

30
00:02:23,745 --> 00:02:24,915
Do you really like Ba Ra?

31
00:02:25,685 --> 00:02:26,715
I do.

32
00:02:26,715 --> 00:02:28,615
Then stop thinking about your feelings.

33
00:02:28,855 --> 00:02:30,955
If you were Ba Ra's actual brother,

34
00:02:31,485 --> 00:02:33,455
and she told you she was dating a man
23 years older than her,

35
00:02:33,795 --> 00:02:35,325
would you say "That's great, go for it"?

36
00:02:35,395 --> 00:02:36,895
You sound just like her actual brother.

37
00:02:37,125 --> 00:02:41,335
Loving someone means you must respect
and consider their feelings, not yours.

38
00:02:41,565 --> 00:02:42,565
That's what real love is.

39
00:02:44,805 --> 00:02:47,775
I think Manager Yoon is perfect for you.

40
00:02:47,775 --> 00:02:48,935
"Perfect" how?

41
00:02:49,305 --> 00:02:50,745
There has to be a spark.

42
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:54,315
Your standards are too high from dealing
with celebrities and their wives so often.

43
00:02:54,315 --> 00:02:55,945
You're not one to talk.

44
00:02:56,715 --> 00:02:58,015
(Ju Shin)

45
00:02:58,315 --> 00:02:59,815
Momo is a commoner.

46
00:03:01,885 --> 00:03:03,825
- Yes?
- So you went to the hospital together?

47
00:03:03,925 --> 00:03:06,155
- Yes.
- His phone was off.

48
00:03:06,355 --> 00:03:07,625
We're having breakfast together now.

49
00:03:07,995 --> 00:03:11,125
Just as I thought, everything's fine.
Tell him he got a clean bill of health.

50
00:03:11,465 --> 00:03:13,935
Okay. And tell him to cut back
on the sugary drinks.

51
00:03:14,495 --> 00:03:16,235
An upset stomach can cause headaches.

52
00:03:16,235 --> 00:03:17,735
Got it. Thanks.

53
00:03:19,035 --> 00:03:20,075
Was that Director Shin?

54
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:27,275
- Hello?
- I don't feel well.

55
00:03:27,445 --> 00:03:28,445
How so?

56
00:03:28,715 --> 00:03:31,785
Could you pick up a pregnancy test
for me tonight?

57
00:03:33,315 --> 00:03:34,315
A pregnancy test.

58
00:03:34,985 --> 00:03:35,985
Okay.

59
00:03:36,355 --> 00:03:37,355
Talk to you later.

60
00:03:44,965 --> 00:03:47,095
Did you marry when you were young?

61
00:03:47,295 --> 00:03:49,165
If you thought
Kim Jin Ju was your daughter...

62
00:03:49,665 --> 00:03:52,405
I wasn't married.
It was back in high school.

63
00:03:53,305 --> 00:03:56,545
- She was a year older than me.
- An older girl?

64
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:58,445
Yes.

65
00:04:00,415 --> 00:04:01,615
We were young and reckless.

66
00:04:02,315 --> 00:04:03,945
She got pregnant during my senior year.

67
00:04:04,985 --> 00:04:07,785
So your girlfriend gave birth
when she was 20?

68
00:04:09,585 --> 00:04:11,655
But then my family's business went under.

69
00:04:12,325 --> 00:04:13,725
After my family went bankrupt,

70
00:04:13,725 --> 00:04:17,625
she left our three-day-old baby
with me in midwinter December...

71
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:18,625
and disappeared.

72
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:20,335
But didn't she have a family?

73
00:04:20,595 --> 00:04:23,335
Even her widowed mother, a cleaner,
didn't know where she went.

74
00:04:24,635 --> 00:04:27,405
Creditors were hounding us,
so my parents went into hiding,

75
00:04:27,575 --> 00:04:31,375
and I crashed at a friend's place
with the baby before moving to Japan.

76
00:04:31,675 --> 00:04:34,245
When you came back,
did you ever hear from the baby's mother?

77
00:04:37,345 --> 00:04:39,185
- You met her?
- I did.

78
00:04:39,815 --> 00:04:41,955
And? Is she doing well?

79
00:04:43,925 --> 00:04:44,925
The thing is...

80
00:04:47,255 --> 00:04:50,525
I'll tell you more once I find my child.

81
00:04:50,965 --> 00:04:52,635
Is she someone I might know?

82
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:00,905
She has to be someone I know.

83
00:05:07,115 --> 00:05:11,515
Can you pull up a list of our clients
between the ages of 47 and 50?

84
00:05:12,015 --> 00:05:14,055
- Both men and women?
- Just the women.

85
00:05:14,255 --> 00:05:15,255
Right away.

86
00:05:17,225 --> 00:05:19,725
Isn't that for Kang Ma Ri?
She doesn't want it?

87
00:05:20,025 --> 00:05:21,525
- That's right.
- What is it now?

88
00:05:21,525 --> 00:05:23,165
She says it makes her arms look big.

89
00:05:23,525 --> 00:05:25,765
That's because her arms are big.

90
00:05:25,965 --> 00:05:27,635
She should lose weight or chop them off.

91
00:05:27,735 --> 00:05:29,565
She said the last one made her look
flat-chested.

92
00:05:29,635 --> 00:05:31,965
She hated the Pedro dress
because it showed the top of her feet.

93
00:05:32,035 --> 00:05:33,105
She's still complaining?

94
00:05:33,105 --> 00:05:35,105
She's the one who stepped on the dress
and fell at the press conference?

95
00:05:36,005 --> 00:05:38,305
I've reached my limit.
Tell her to find another sponsor.

96
00:05:39,075 --> 00:05:40,075
Are you serious?

97
00:05:40,515 --> 00:05:41,515
Yes.

98
00:05:50,685 --> 00:05:52,225
(Director Shin)

99
00:05:56,525 --> 00:05:57,525
Hello?

100
00:05:57,895 --> 00:05:58,895
Is now a good time to talk?

101
00:05:59,295 --> 00:06:01,495
- Yes.
- Do you have time to meet?

102
00:06:02,065 --> 00:06:03,565
I wanted to ask you about the orphanage.

103
00:06:04,265 --> 00:06:05,265
I'd like to get your advice.

104
00:06:06,175 --> 00:06:07,975
- Okay.
- Today.

105
00:06:08,205 --> 00:06:09,875
I'm booked until the day after tomorrow.

106
00:06:10,575 --> 00:06:12,175
- Wednesday.
- Yes.

107
00:07:19,615 --> 00:07:20,615
Were you right?

108
00:07:23,345 --> 00:07:25,545
Goodness. Congratulations!

109
00:07:27,355 --> 00:07:28,355
Congratulations?

110
00:07:29,685 --> 00:07:31,425
You two are getting married anyway.

111
00:07:31,425 --> 00:07:32,925
I'm not ready for that.

112
00:07:33,855 --> 00:07:35,825
Just hurry up and have the wedding.

113
00:07:36,295 --> 00:07:37,765
I don't want to have it.

114
00:07:41,035 --> 00:07:43,265
Director Shin would be so happy.

115
00:07:43,805 --> 00:07:44,835
Who cares?

116
00:07:45,365 --> 00:07:48,305
This is the sky's way of helping you
forget your sorrows with a new life.

117
00:07:48,475 --> 00:07:50,745
It's a gift
so that you can be happy again.

118
00:07:53,215 --> 00:07:55,375
Are you saying all mothers are happy?

119
00:07:58,845 --> 00:08:00,815
If you ever need help, ask anytime.

120
00:08:00,815 --> 00:08:01,855
I don't need any.

121
00:08:01,855 --> 00:08:02,855
You really don't get people, do you?

122
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:04,825
Don't jump to conclusions.

123
00:08:11,165 --> 00:08:12,265
It's not my baby.

124
00:08:13,065 --> 00:08:14,165
How could it be mine?

125
00:08:17,935 --> 00:08:20,905
- Knock before you come in.
- But the door was open.

126
00:08:21,235 --> 00:08:22,275
Close them.

127
00:08:57,205 --> 00:08:58,275
Hello.

128
00:09:01,045 --> 00:09:02,145
That's not me.

129
00:09:03,085 --> 00:09:04,515
I heard that person quit.

130
00:09:06,785 --> 00:09:08,255
What's your relationship to her?

131
00:09:09,385 --> 00:09:10,385
I'm her father.

132
00:09:18,195 --> 00:09:21,335
When I saw how startled you were,
I started thinking,

133
00:09:21,765 --> 00:09:24,005
and I wondered if you had some trouble
when you lived at the orphanage.

134
00:09:27,735 --> 00:09:28,735
Am I right?

135
00:09:29,275 --> 00:09:31,075
After the director passed away,

136
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:35,345
have you happened to visit the orphanage?

137
00:09:38,215 --> 00:09:39,585
The babies and toddlers...

138
00:09:40,885 --> 00:09:42,455
are especially heartbreaking to see.

139
00:09:44,325 --> 00:09:46,425
They play some lullaby-like music,

140
00:09:46,555 --> 00:09:49,925
and it's already sad seeing
two or three babies napping together,

141
00:09:50,665 --> 00:09:52,395
but imagine
if there's thunder and lightning.

142
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:54,465
The babies get absolutely terrified.

143
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:59,735
I wish they could hire more caregivers,
at least for the nursery.

144
00:10:01,235 --> 00:10:02,275
So they're like aunts to the kids?

145
00:10:02,675 --> 00:10:03,675
Yes.

146
00:10:06,475 --> 00:10:07,515
Have some.

147
00:10:14,985 --> 00:10:15,985
You don't care for wine?

148
00:10:18,525 --> 00:10:19,525
No, that's not it.

149
00:10:24,525 --> 00:10:27,395
To be honest,
I don't really know much about wine.

150
00:10:35,905 --> 00:10:37,475
May I tell you a bit more?

151
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:42,275
You know you're not supposed to
let toddlers watch things on a phone.

152
00:10:43,115 --> 00:10:44,145
Of course not.

153
00:10:44,785 --> 00:10:46,455
You should bring it up
with the office manager directly.

154
00:10:46,555 --> 00:10:49,415
I tried talking to the office manager
about it after I left.

155
00:10:50,485 --> 00:10:51,925
He said they don't have
the resources for it.

156
00:10:52,455 --> 00:10:55,295
I guess you don't get involved
in these matters at all.

157
00:10:55,695 --> 00:10:56,825
It's not so much that I don't.

158
00:10:58,265 --> 00:11:01,195
The office manager has been in charge
of running things since my father's day.

159
00:11:01,495 --> 00:11:02,695
And we have advisors, too.

160
00:11:03,665 --> 00:11:06,535
Well, it's a relief that
you're taking an interest now.

161
00:11:06,835 --> 00:11:08,275
You make a donation every month,
don't you?

162
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:10,445
I saw your name on the donor list.

163
00:11:11,205 --> 00:11:12,915
As I mentioned last time,

164
00:11:13,415 --> 00:11:16,215
I wouldn't be where I am today
without the Nua Foundation.

165
00:11:16,745 --> 00:11:19,085
I just want to give back
a little something...

166
00:11:19,545 --> 00:11:22,055
Have you thought about quitting reporting
and taking over the orphanage?

167
00:11:22,885 --> 00:11:23,885
As the director?

168
00:11:24,555 --> 00:11:27,355
- That's out of the question.
- Why is it out of the question?

169
00:11:27,795 --> 00:11:28,855
You're more than qualified.

170
00:11:30,925 --> 00:11:33,165
Didn't Momo tell you?

171
00:11:36,305 --> 00:11:39,735
I'm leaving my job at the end
of the month to help Momo out.

172
00:11:40,535 --> 00:11:41,675
You're going to be her manager?

173
00:11:42,435 --> 00:11:43,745
You're quitting the paper for that?

174
00:11:44,445 --> 00:11:46,775
She says she needs someone
who can be like family.

175
00:11:47,275 --> 00:11:48,445
That's why.

176
00:11:48,775 --> 00:11:49,985
Momo's offer...

177
00:11:50,245 --> 00:11:53,355
is for me to officially take over
and run the gallery in two to three years.

178
00:11:53,915 --> 00:11:55,215
But above all,

179
00:11:56,725 --> 00:11:58,255
I don't have anyone either.

180
00:11:58,755 --> 00:11:59,755
Are you lonely?

181
00:12:01,525 --> 00:12:02,625
Why did I ask something obvious?

182
00:12:03,395 --> 00:12:05,625
I have a soft spot
for people younger than me.

183
00:12:07,895 --> 00:12:09,665
So you're saying you're tough
on Yong Joong and me?

184
00:12:17,705 --> 00:12:21,975
Also, it would be nice
to let the girls grow their hair out.

185
00:12:22,245 --> 00:12:25,945
- They're forbidden to?
- It's high maintenance and hard to wash.

186
00:12:32,925 --> 00:12:36,565
I was always so envious
of the girls with long hair,

187
00:12:37,195 --> 00:12:41,065
watching them braid it,
tie it up, and put in pins.

188
00:12:41,665 --> 00:12:43,635
I'd find myself staring
for the longest time.

189
00:12:44,205 --> 00:12:46,135
Long hair suits you.

190
00:12:46,775 --> 00:12:48,375
I cut a lot off when I started this job.

191
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:49,605
How long did it used to be?

192
00:12:49,705 --> 00:12:51,045
Below my waist.

193
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,115
Do you have a picture?

194
00:13:02,255 --> 00:13:04,255
What was your mother like?

195
00:13:04,925 --> 00:13:07,795
She was incredibly devoted
to my dad and me.

196
00:13:07,795 --> 00:13:10,365
You call him "Dad" too.

197
00:13:10,525 --> 00:13:11,525
Who else?

198
00:13:13,065 --> 00:13:14,065
Yong Joong?

199
00:13:16,905 --> 00:13:18,605
It sounds so affectionate.

200
00:13:22,535 --> 00:13:24,105
In what way was she devoted?

201
00:13:25,575 --> 00:13:26,975
She was wise, I'd say.

202
00:13:28,545 --> 00:13:29,945
She never graduated from college.

203
00:13:31,145 --> 00:13:33,215
She met my dad during her sophomore year,
and they got married.

204
00:13:35,655 --> 00:13:38,625
Do you take after your mother
or your father?

205
00:13:39,185 --> 00:13:40,725
- In looks?
- In personality.

206
00:13:40,795 --> 00:13:41,925
I don't take after my father, do I?

207
00:13:44,725 --> 00:13:45,895
What's that nod for?

208
00:13:47,135 --> 00:13:48,135
No reason.

209
00:13:48,865 --> 00:13:50,205
And I'm nothing like my mother, either.

210
00:13:51,505 --> 00:13:56,035
You and your father visited the orphanage
when I was in elementary school.

211
00:13:56,275 --> 00:13:57,945
This might sound a little strange, but...

212
00:13:58,545 --> 00:14:01,275
You were just so elegant and graceful.

213
00:14:02,075 --> 00:14:03,245
Doctor...

214
00:14:04,415 --> 00:14:05,885
This might sound a little strange, but...

215
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:08,855
Your looks are kind of wasted
on just your patients.

216
00:14:09,785 --> 00:14:11,255
Have you ever been scouted?

217
00:14:14,795 --> 00:14:15,995
Have I lost it all now?

218
00:14:16,495 --> 00:14:17,695
You even talk like that?

219
00:14:17,895 --> 00:14:18,925
Don't change the subject.

220
00:14:19,395 --> 00:14:20,635
Do I look worn out,
beaten down by the world?

221
00:14:21,565 --> 00:14:22,565
No.

222
00:14:23,035 --> 00:14:26,135
Then and now,
you've always been hard to approach.

223
00:14:29,845 --> 00:14:31,105
What's your type?

224
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:35,775
- I haven't thought about it.
- That would be a lie.

225
00:14:36,615 --> 00:14:39,145
I think most women are
pretty much the same.

226
00:14:39,415 --> 00:14:41,115
A man who's thoughtful and caring.

227
00:14:41,785 --> 00:14:45,425
No. I know plenty of women
who like bad boys.

228
00:14:46,895 --> 00:14:47,925
What about me?

229
00:14:48,655 --> 00:14:49,755
The mean type?

230
00:14:49,895 --> 00:14:52,125
There's a difference between being mean
and being a bad person.

231
00:14:52,425 --> 00:14:54,295
And just because someone's cold
doesn't mean they're a bad person.

232
00:14:55,165 --> 00:14:56,765
You do a lot of good, after all.

233
00:14:57,405 --> 00:14:58,865
Through your hospital and the foundation.

234
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,205
Honestly, it's overwhelming.

235
00:15:08,845 --> 00:15:10,915
I'm sure most people are...

236
00:15:11,215 --> 00:15:13,255
if they're determined to live life
the right way.

237
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:21,225
In ten years,
I'll offer you the director's position.

238
00:15:29,065 --> 00:15:30,665
We should do this from time to time.

239
00:15:31,405 --> 00:15:32,865
And please continue to look after
the foundation.

240
00:15:33,135 --> 00:15:34,135
Okay.

241
00:15:41,915 --> 00:15:44,645
Can we get another carpaccio?

242
00:15:44,645 --> 00:15:46,045
- Another one.
- Yes, sir.

243
00:15:48,355 --> 00:15:49,455
It's nice to see you eat so well.

244
00:15:49,755 --> 00:15:51,425
This is on a whole other level.

245
00:15:53,425 --> 00:15:55,695
We'd sometimes get bulgogi
at the orphanage,

246
00:15:56,725 --> 00:15:59,495
but the meat didn't even seem to be
imported beef.

247
00:15:59,865 --> 00:16:01,365
To put it bluntly,

248
00:16:01,935 --> 00:16:03,905
it was like eating stir-fried tire.

249
00:16:06,035 --> 00:16:07,435
I take back saying
we should do this again.

250
00:16:08,005 --> 00:16:09,235
You'll bankrupt the foundation.

251
00:16:12,105 --> 00:16:13,475
What kind of mom do you want to be?

252
00:16:15,075 --> 00:16:16,245
I'd have to get married first.

253
00:16:17,585 --> 00:16:18,585
You're not the marrying type?

254
00:16:19,315 --> 00:16:21,185
I guess that's probably how it'll be.

255
00:16:21,985 --> 00:16:23,115
Why so hesitant?

256
00:16:23,685 --> 00:16:26,455
- But you're so confident and smart.
- I'm just good at faking it.

257
00:16:28,055 --> 00:16:31,665
When Momo has her baby,
I'll be happy just to be its aunt.

258
00:16:33,935 --> 00:16:35,035
Let me rephrase the question.

259
00:16:36,535 --> 00:16:37,735
What kind of aunt do you want to be?

260
00:16:38,705 --> 00:16:39,935
The fun aunt.

261
00:16:40,975 --> 00:16:43,445
You and Momo can be the villains,

262
00:16:44,345 --> 00:16:45,775
and I'll just be the one
who spoils the kid.

263
00:16:52,145 --> 00:16:55,115
(The Humanities of Discovery)

264
00:17:00,195 --> 00:17:01,755
Looks like she's busy again today.

265
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,635
I wonder what the housekeeper
left for us to eat.

266
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:37,825
Give me back my head.

267
00:17:38,365 --> 00:17:39,665
Give me back my head.

268
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:40,835
My head...

269
00:17:51,275 --> 00:17:52,745
I am not Momo.

270
00:17:54,575 --> 00:17:56,345
This is only Momo's body.

271
00:17:56,945 --> 00:18:00,385
- What is she talking about?
- Inside my head, my brain...

272
00:18:01,515 --> 00:18:04,585
is that of Geum Ba Ra,
a reporter for the Sungwoo Daily.

273
00:18:05,225 --> 00:18:06,285
For real?

274
00:18:07,255 --> 00:18:09,655
Everyone,
have you ever heard of a brain swap?

275
00:18:10,695 --> 00:18:11,695
It is possible.

276
00:18:12,665 --> 00:18:14,935
And the mastermind
with the divine touch is...

277
00:18:16,565 --> 00:18:19,105
Director Shin Ju Shin
of Nua General Hospital.

278
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:22,935
- This is absurd.
- Seriously?

279
00:18:30,645 --> 00:18:32,615
Oh my, what is that?

280
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:34,655
Is that really the scar? No way...

281
00:18:40,095 --> 00:18:41,955
- Please, open the door!
- Director Shin!

282
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:43,995
(My daughter has a brain tumor.)

283
00:18:44,065 --> 00:18:45,665
(Give my brain to my daughter,
Director Shin Ju Shin)

284
00:18:45,725 --> 00:18:46,835
(My older brother is brain-dead.)

285
00:18:46,835 --> 00:18:49,195
(I don't want to live,
so please save my brother, Director Shin!)

286
00:18:49,335 --> 00:18:50,765
(My wife wants to die
because of her depression.)

287
00:18:50,765 --> 00:18:52,635
(Her mother is in a nursing home
and could pass any day. Please, Director.)

288
00:18:52,635 --> 00:18:54,605
- Director Shin Ju Shin!
- My brother is brain-dead!

289
00:18:54,735 --> 00:18:55,935
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

290
00:18:56,005 --> 00:18:57,845
Please save my mother-in-law.

291
00:18:59,305 --> 00:19:01,045
Please, Doctor!

292
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:07,585
- Please save my mother-in-law.
- Please save her, Director.

293
00:19:10,385 --> 00:19:12,255
- Please, save her, Director!
- Director!

294
00:19:12,785 --> 00:19:15,055
- Director!
- Please, help us!

295
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:16,765
Help me, please!

296
00:19:29,005 --> 00:19:31,605
Shin Ju Shin, you're under arrest
for the murder of Kim Jin Ju.

297
00:19:55,665 --> 00:19:57,665
It doesn't look like
the director knows yet.

298
00:19:58,005 --> 00:19:59,835
- Why didn't you tell him?
- You met him?

299
00:19:59,905 --> 00:20:00,905
Yesterday.

300
00:20:01,235 --> 00:20:04,075
- Why?
- He asked about the orphanage.

301
00:20:04,445 --> 00:20:07,675
- Now that he's the foundation's chairman.
- The manager...

302
00:20:08,245 --> 00:20:11,015
He has a manager for that, doesn't he?
He can just get a report.

303
00:20:11,915 --> 00:20:14,185
There are things you can get
from a manager's report,

304
00:20:14,185 --> 00:20:16,925
and things you only hear
from someone who was there.

305
00:20:21,055 --> 00:20:22,095
I'm not having it.

306
00:20:22,595 --> 00:20:23,695
That's ridiculous.

307
00:20:26,065 --> 00:20:27,635
This isn't a decision
you get to make alone.

308
00:20:27,965 --> 00:20:30,095
- What if he wants me to have it?
- Obviously.

309
00:20:33,705 --> 00:20:35,735
At least talk to him about it.

310
00:20:36,035 --> 00:20:37,575
My life is over if I have this baby.

311
00:20:37,575 --> 00:20:39,875
Over? Not everyone gets to be a mother.

312
00:20:47,015 --> 00:20:48,155
What time do you usually go to bed?

313
00:20:48,515 --> 00:20:52,325
My articles go live early in the morning,
so I try to be in bed before midnight.

314
00:20:54,725 --> 00:20:56,895
The chef is asking
if there's anything else you need.

315
00:20:59,495 --> 00:21:00,495
I'm full.

316
00:21:01,995 --> 00:21:04,005
- Check, please.
- It's already been taken care of.

317
00:21:04,465 --> 00:21:05,505
It has?

318
00:21:07,605 --> 00:21:08,605
When?

319
00:21:10,705 --> 00:21:13,205
When I stepped out
to take that call earlier.

320
00:21:16,575 --> 00:21:17,745
I'm the one who asked you to dinner.

321
00:21:18,045 --> 00:21:20,315
Buying you this meal
is the least I could do.

322
00:21:20,555 --> 00:21:23,285
The Nua Children's Home
may have fed you terrible meat,

323
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:25,155
but they sure raised you right.

324
00:21:26,325 --> 00:21:27,695
Next time, I'm treating you properly.

325
00:21:28,725 --> 00:21:31,825
I know a great Hanwoo omakase place.
It's members-only.

326
00:21:31,995 --> 00:21:33,935
I didn't realize you were such a foodie.

327
00:21:34,335 --> 00:21:35,495
I wouldn't say I'm a foodie.

328
00:21:36,165 --> 00:21:37,405
What do you do for stress?

329
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:40,065
Just working is how I relieve stress.

330
00:21:40,335 --> 00:21:42,035
If you're that satisfied with your job,

331
00:21:42,705 --> 00:21:43,875
you can't just quit.

332
00:21:44,445 --> 00:21:47,715
If I were the one
who desperately needed help,

333
00:21:48,045 --> 00:21:49,475
I'd be heartbroken
if someone turned their back on me.

334
00:21:51,945 --> 00:21:52,985
Do you trust people?

335
00:21:53,515 --> 00:21:54,815
I have to, at first.

336
00:21:57,885 --> 00:21:59,855
But I never want to be betrayed.

337
00:22:01,155 --> 00:22:02,155
What if they do?

338
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:03,965
What happens then?

339
00:22:06,395 --> 00:22:07,795
I cut them out of my heart.

340
00:22:10,095 --> 00:22:11,135
I'd better be careful.

341
00:22:34,595 --> 00:22:36,755
- Yes, Director Shin.
- When are you free?

342
00:22:37,325 --> 00:22:38,625
I need to make
a reservation at the restaurant.

343
00:22:40,195 --> 00:22:42,595
Can I check my schedule and text you?

344
00:22:43,495 --> 00:22:45,305
Is it your bedtime?

345
00:22:46,665 --> 00:22:48,705
- Sorry.
- No, not yet.

346
00:22:49,135 --> 00:22:50,775
What about you, Director Shin?
What time do you go to bed?

347
00:22:52,275 --> 00:22:53,645
I'm wide awake at this hour.

348
00:23:00,915 --> 00:23:03,255
(Momo)

349
00:23:05,625 --> 00:23:07,625
- Yes.
- Can I come up?

350
00:23:09,855 --> 00:23:10,995
Is something wrong?

351
00:23:13,695 --> 00:23:15,035
I'm pregnant.

352
00:23:17,635 --> 00:23:19,605
I was feeling off,
so I took a pregnancy test.

353
00:23:20,675 --> 00:23:21,705
Are you sure?

354
00:23:22,505 --> 00:23:24,005
Those can be inaccurate.

355
00:23:27,315 --> 00:23:29,675
If it's positive,
we should terminate it, right?

356
00:23:33,655 --> 00:23:34,655
No.

357
00:23:36,355 --> 00:23:39,085
I just had surgery,
and I've been on all these antibiotics...

358
00:23:39,155 --> 00:23:40,955
They're still born
perfectly normal and healthy.

359
00:23:43,355 --> 00:23:44,925
- What if...
- Don't even go there.

360
00:23:46,625 --> 00:23:47,635
You're having the baby.

361
00:23:51,305 --> 00:23:53,565
It'll be bad for our public image...

362
00:23:53,565 --> 00:23:54,935
We're publicly engaged.

363
00:23:56,505 --> 00:23:57,505
You're having the baby.

364
00:23:59,745 --> 00:24:01,575
You don't seem very happy.

365
00:24:06,545 --> 00:24:09,185
I'm just in shock. I wasn't expecting it.

366
00:24:09,655 --> 00:24:11,955
It doesn't even feel like my baby.

367
00:24:12,755 --> 00:24:13,895
By that logic,

368
00:24:14,725 --> 00:24:15,925
are you never going to have kids?

369
00:24:17,765 --> 00:24:19,825
I'm not ready for this now.

370
00:24:20,435 --> 00:24:22,235
I've never even thought about it.

371
00:24:23,565 --> 00:24:25,335
Then start thinking and preparing now.

372
00:24:26,335 --> 00:24:27,835
And you must be diligent
with your prenatal care.

373
00:24:39,485 --> 00:24:40,615
I'll be more attentive.

374
00:24:40,985 --> 00:24:44,355
I had a scary dream
when I was waking up from the anesthesia.

375
00:24:45,785 --> 00:24:46,985
I guess it was a conception dream.

376
00:24:49,555 --> 00:24:50,565
What dream?

377
00:25:01,335 --> 00:25:02,335
Paul.

378
00:25:05,945 --> 00:25:08,545
I saw this outfit and thought of you.

379
00:25:09,045 --> 00:25:10,985
I thought it would look amazing on you.

380
00:25:11,245 --> 00:25:13,645
Thank you, but I can't just accept this.

381
00:25:14,355 --> 00:25:16,315
Clothes are all I have to give.

382
00:25:16,885 --> 00:25:19,385
It was sponsored for one of my actors,
so it's not new.

383
00:25:19,385 --> 00:25:21,695
It'll just collect dust in my closet.

384
00:25:21,825 --> 00:25:23,355
A huge movie star wore this.

385
00:25:25,065 --> 00:25:27,495
(Seoul)

386
00:25:34,335 --> 00:25:36,905
Are you planning to stay single forever?

387
00:25:39,245 --> 00:25:40,245
Yes.

388
00:25:40,675 --> 00:25:43,545
But we're both in our prime.

389
00:25:49,785 --> 00:25:51,985
I can't trust women.

390
00:25:52,925 --> 00:25:54,295
They're just not trustworthy.

391
00:25:55,825 --> 00:25:58,765
They'll leave you in a heartbeat
if they think you've got nothing to offer.

392
00:25:59,125 --> 00:26:00,665
That's not always true.

393
00:26:01,635 --> 00:26:04,665
There are plenty of kind,
wonderful women out there.

394
00:26:06,435 --> 00:26:08,835
Have you ever seen a fortune teller?

395
00:26:10,705 --> 00:26:11,975
Is any of that stuff ever right?

396
00:26:12,375 --> 00:26:13,645
They can be.

397
00:26:13,915 --> 00:26:15,015
So what did they say about you?

398
00:26:15,315 --> 00:26:17,345
That I'm destined to get married
within five years,

399
00:26:18,045 --> 00:26:20,385
and that my soulmate is a younger woman,
old enough to be my daughter.

400
00:26:20,715 --> 00:26:23,655
- Really?
- And then she appeared right before me.

401
00:26:25,385 --> 00:26:27,555
- A young woman?
- Yes.

402
00:26:27,625 --> 00:26:28,625
And then what?

403
00:26:31,195 --> 00:26:33,495
After agonizing over it by myself,
I decided to let it go.

404
00:26:33,765 --> 00:26:36,165
Why? It could've been fate.

405
00:26:36,265 --> 00:26:38,865
I don't think so.
She doesn't see me that way at all.

406
00:26:40,735 --> 00:26:42,335
Well, they did say five years.

407
00:26:43,305 --> 00:26:44,675
You should wait and see.

408
00:26:45,605 --> 00:26:47,975
You never know what life has in store.

409
00:26:48,475 --> 00:26:50,115
Take Kim Jin Ju, for example.

410
00:26:52,545 --> 00:26:54,085
And CEO Hyun Ran Hee, too.

411
00:26:55,685 --> 00:26:57,585
You've met CEO Hyun, right?

412
00:26:58,085 --> 00:27:00,085
She asked for your number,
so I gave it to her.

413
00:27:00,855 --> 00:27:01,855
Yes.

414
00:27:02,595 --> 00:27:03,925
Did she buy one of your pieces?

415
00:27:07,095 --> 00:27:08,095
Yes.

416
00:27:09,465 --> 00:27:10,635
By the way,

417
00:27:11,005 --> 00:27:13,735
can't you tell me who your first love was?

418
00:27:14,175 --> 00:27:15,435
I won't tell a soul.

419
00:27:18,945 --> 00:27:19,975
Some other time.

420
00:27:22,275 --> 00:27:23,445
Are you still looking for your child?

421
00:27:23,745 --> 00:27:25,085
I'll never give up.

422
00:27:27,385 --> 00:27:28,555
As long as my child is alive.

423
00:27:30,285 --> 00:27:31,325
Somehow.

424
00:27:31,625 --> 00:27:32,955
Do you know the exact time
your child was born?

425
00:27:33,995 --> 00:27:34,995
If you do...

426
00:27:35,755 --> 00:27:37,125
Well, I'm not talking
about some divine act,

427
00:27:38,765 --> 00:27:41,635
but a fortune teller might be able
to find something out for you.

428
00:27:50,875 --> 00:27:51,905
Hey, Yong Joong.

429
00:27:52,375 --> 00:27:55,375
- Did you pick up Pickles?
- Yes, the housekeeper was just leaving.

430
00:27:55,745 --> 00:27:56,815
You should've just waited.

431
00:27:57,485 --> 00:27:58,515
I'm on my way now.

432
00:27:58,945 --> 00:28:01,415
I'm at Momo's place.
I wanted to show her Pickles.

433
00:28:05,655 --> 00:28:06,685
You should come, too.

434
00:28:08,425 --> 00:28:09,425
No, it's okay.

435
00:28:11,665 --> 00:28:14,465
I'm sure Momo won't mind. I'll ask her.

436
00:28:16,065 --> 00:28:17,565
Pickles.

437
00:28:18,165 --> 00:28:20,635
You're so fancy.
Why would anyone abandon you?

438
00:28:26,975 --> 00:28:29,245
Momo says we should all order some food.

439
00:28:40,855 --> 00:28:42,195
(Today was another tough day.)

440
00:29:13,355 --> 00:29:15,295
Today was another tough day.

441
00:29:16,155 --> 00:29:18,425
No one talked to me,

442
00:29:18,725 --> 00:29:22,565
and even though I got first place,
my homeroom teacher didn't praise me.

443
00:29:23,135 --> 00:29:25,405
She was probably hoping
Park Ji Ah would take first.

444
00:29:26,665 --> 00:29:29,935
Whenever I feel sad or treated unfairly...

445
00:29:30,375 --> 00:29:32,905
and heartbreaking tears
well up in my eyes,

446
00:29:33,405 --> 00:29:35,915
I get through it
by thinking of Yong Joong.

447
00:29:36,845 --> 00:29:38,515
His warm embrace...

448
00:29:39,115 --> 00:29:40,715
is unforgettable.

449
00:29:41,255 --> 00:29:43,315
The warmth has been etched
into my very soul.

450
00:29:44,385 --> 00:29:46,025
I'll become someone amazing...

451
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,325
and then go see him again.

452
00:30:22,295 --> 00:30:23,295
Are we going out to eat?

453
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:24,965
No.

454
00:30:40,305 --> 00:30:41,315
Welcome.

455
00:30:43,375 --> 00:30:44,385
Oh my.

456
00:30:46,645 --> 00:30:47,785
You shouldn't have.

457
00:30:47,985 --> 00:30:49,755
I saw a flower shop in the building.

458
00:30:49,955 --> 00:30:52,355
This is perfect.
I was all out of flowers and dessert.

459
00:30:54,195 --> 00:30:55,355
There's a vase in the kitchen.

460
00:30:57,965 --> 00:30:58,965
Put this in the fridge.

461
00:31:02,995 --> 00:31:04,405
We can have that for dessert.

462
00:31:05,935 --> 00:31:06,935
Please, have a seat.

463
00:31:12,605 --> 00:31:13,805
Look how much he likes you.

464
00:31:14,775 --> 00:31:15,815
Hey, Pickles.

465
00:31:19,185 --> 00:31:20,915
That breed's pretty rare here, isn't it?

466
00:31:22,585 --> 00:31:23,585
Yes.

467
00:31:24,955 --> 00:31:25,955
What are you in the mood for?

468
00:31:26,225 --> 00:31:28,055
There's a place
that has great eel rice bowls.

469
00:31:28,525 --> 00:31:29,725
I'll leave it up to you, Momo.

470
00:31:30,355 --> 00:31:31,695
I'm not a picky eater.

471
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:33,895
I'm so bad at deciding.

472
00:31:34,495 --> 00:31:36,195
- Ba Ra!
- I'll do it.

473
00:31:49,715 --> 00:31:50,775
And some sushi, too.

474
00:31:51,345 --> 00:31:52,345
For two.

475
00:31:56,015 --> 00:31:57,315
Does Pickles eat salmon?

476
00:31:57,885 --> 00:31:58,885
He does.

477
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,125
You must be a total pro at games.

478
00:32:05,565 --> 00:32:06,665
I wouldn't go that far.

479
00:32:07,465 --> 00:32:10,035
Developing them is different
from playing them for fun.

480
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:12,105
I'm terrible at games.

481
00:32:13,265 --> 00:32:14,535
I can't act.

482
00:32:16,605 --> 00:32:20,475
Company helps me laugh and feel at ease.
It really does.

483
00:32:21,245 --> 00:32:23,145
But I can't just invite anyone over,
you know?

484
00:32:24,785 --> 00:32:28,255
Apparently, a hidden camera was installed
at my friend Yoo Kyung's place.

485
00:32:29,015 --> 00:32:31,085
Don't tell me it was an acquaintance
who put it there.

486
00:32:33,755 --> 00:32:37,625
Apparently, the housekeeper always watched
any repairmen who came over.

487
00:32:38,725 --> 00:32:41,165
So now, Yoo Kyung doesn't invite
anyone over anymore.

488
00:32:41,535 --> 00:32:43,095
She only attends parties outside her home.

489
00:32:43,835 --> 00:32:45,335
It might look glamorous on the outside,

490
00:32:46,165 --> 00:32:49,675
but it's an exhausting and lonely job.

491
00:32:53,505 --> 00:32:54,515
Mr. Ha.

492
00:32:55,315 --> 00:32:59,545
I'm just going to call you Yong Joong
from now on.

493
00:32:59,745 --> 00:33:00,745
Let's drop the formalities.

494
00:33:01,455 --> 00:33:04,385
"Mr. Ha" makes me uncomfortable too.

495
00:33:06,185 --> 00:33:08,455
I bet you get to do everything
you want in life.

496
00:33:10,425 --> 00:33:11,595
Is there...

497
00:33:12,095 --> 00:33:13,365
anything you've wanted to do?

498
00:33:13,995 --> 00:33:18,205
I'd love to just drive to the coast,
like in Gangwon Province.

499
00:33:19,705 --> 00:33:20,735
Then you should go.

500
00:33:21,375 --> 00:33:22,675
I'm not confident enough.

501
00:33:23,275 --> 00:33:24,945
I've only ever pretended to drive
for a role.

502
00:33:26,305 --> 00:33:29,015
And Director Shin Ju Shin
is always so busy.

503
00:33:30,275 --> 00:33:31,985
Let's go today for some driving practice.

504
00:33:39,085 --> 00:33:41,295
I have to watch Pickles.

505
00:33:43,055 --> 00:33:45,125
Is it about a three-hour drive
to Gangneung?

506
00:33:45,795 --> 00:33:47,025
There's no traffic at night.

507
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:52,135
Pickles, let's go.

508
00:33:52,335 --> 00:33:53,535
At least eat dinner first.

509
00:34:04,545 --> 00:34:06,715
I'm almost there. Be ready to go out.

510
00:34:09,385 --> 00:34:10,555
Ju Shin is on his way.

511
00:34:11,055 --> 00:34:13,225
He told me to get ready
because we're going out.

512
00:34:13,485 --> 00:34:15,955
- A restaurant?
- Then he would've asked if I'd eaten.

513
00:34:21,735 --> 00:34:23,365
We should get going.

514
00:34:24,805 --> 00:34:27,605
- At least say hi.
- You can't freeze sushi, so take it.

515
00:34:30,935 --> 00:34:33,075
I can't pick an outfit
if I don't know where we're going.

516
00:34:40,215 --> 00:34:43,115
You can go to Gangwon Province anytime.

517
00:34:49,855 --> 00:34:51,865
At least you got to see each other...

518
00:34:54,765 --> 00:34:55,765
Hello?

519
00:34:58,765 --> 00:34:59,805
Yes, speaking.

520
00:35:02,935 --> 00:35:04,305
I'm not doing any interviews.

521
00:35:06,945 --> 00:35:08,775
I just said she was my cousin back then.

522
00:35:13,015 --> 00:35:14,045
I'm sorry.

523
00:35:14,885 --> 00:35:16,385
How about we grab a meal sometime instead?

524
00:35:16,385 --> 00:35:17,415
It will be my treat.

525
00:35:19,725 --> 00:35:20,725
Okay.

526
00:35:22,655 --> 00:35:23,655
All right.

527
00:35:29,595 --> 00:35:30,595
Water.

528
00:35:59,925 --> 00:36:02,095
- Hungry?
- Not really.

529
00:36:02,365 --> 00:36:04,735
Then why are you cutting it?
Momo is going out too.

530
00:36:07,535 --> 00:36:08,575
I'm going to freeze it.

531
00:36:10,205 --> 00:36:12,775
Don't worry.
I don't like Shine Muscat cake.

532
00:36:20,885 --> 00:36:22,015
That's not what I meant.

533
00:36:23,415 --> 00:36:24,425
What do you mean?

534
00:36:45,605 --> 00:36:46,605
Is that how you do it?

535
00:36:49,815 --> 00:36:50,815
Let me do it.

536
00:36:52,145 --> 00:36:53,215
Wash your hands first.

537
00:37:13,835 --> 00:37:15,035
Should we get going?

538
00:37:38,165 --> 00:37:40,165
I think Pickles has to go...

539
00:37:47,005 --> 00:37:50,405
- You're were here?
- Yes, with Yong Joong.

540
00:37:51,705 --> 00:37:53,245
It looks like he needs to go.

541
00:37:53,805 --> 00:37:55,375
Just put a pad down for him
in the bathroom.

542
00:38:20,905 --> 00:38:22,205
- Thank you.
- No problem.

543
00:38:22,975 --> 00:38:24,105
Where are we going?

544
00:38:24,545 --> 00:38:25,605
For an ultrasound.

545
00:38:28,145 --> 00:38:29,375
I guess you guys ordered dinner?

546
00:38:30,175 --> 00:38:31,175
Then eat before you go.

547
00:38:34,415 --> 00:38:35,715
Put something down for him
in the bathroom.

548
00:38:49,195 --> 00:38:50,295
Did you guys know I was coming?

549
00:38:50,635 --> 00:38:52,105
We ordered plenty for four.

550
00:38:55,075 --> 00:38:56,075
Are you not feeling well?

551
00:39:06,085 --> 00:39:07,185
We're going for a pregnancy ultrasound.

552
00:39:16,225 --> 00:39:17,355
Aren't you going to use any sauce?

553
00:39:31,575 --> 00:39:32,805
This is so embarrassing.

554
00:39:37,615 --> 00:39:38,645
The car's in the basement.

555
00:39:42,785 --> 00:39:43,815
I called a cab.

556
00:39:45,885 --> 00:39:46,885
Why?

557
00:39:47,355 --> 00:39:49,955
His fur gets everywhere.
And he might scratch your expensive car.

558
00:39:50,125 --> 00:39:51,255
It's not like it's his first time
in my car.

559
00:39:56,695 --> 00:39:57,795
Are you upset about something?

560
00:39:59,335 --> 00:40:00,335
No.

561
00:40:02,035 --> 00:40:03,735
I'll keep him over the weekend.

562
00:40:04,435 --> 00:40:05,445
Hold on.

563
00:40:05,875 --> 00:40:07,075
My cab is here.

564
00:40:18,085 --> 00:40:19,785
(Nua General Hospital)

565
00:40:21,625 --> 00:40:25,695
(Congratulations on this new life!)

566
00:40:25,825 --> 00:40:27,265
This will feel a little cold.

567
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:50,715
(Pet-friendly ride)

568
00:41:09,005 --> 00:41:11,505
You know most drivers don't like
having dogs in their cars.

569
00:41:11,845 --> 00:41:14,245
There's a special taxi service for dogs.

570
00:41:14,975 --> 00:41:16,145
They have taxis like that?

571
00:41:16,445 --> 00:41:17,515
Yes.

572
00:41:22,215 --> 00:41:23,585
The doors are closing.

573
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:29,195
You're just going to leave me?

574
00:41:32,665 --> 00:41:35,295
You came all this way.
Come up and have some fruit.

575
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:43,205
(Jaeil Apartments)

576
00:41:43,775 --> 00:41:45,405
The doors are closing.

577
00:41:50,275 --> 00:41:52,085
Pickles. Wait.

578
00:41:55,715 --> 00:41:56,755
Wet wipes.

579
00:42:11,565 --> 00:42:12,665
You'll spoil him.

580
00:42:14,235 --> 00:42:15,605
I don't give him one when we're alone.

581
00:42:24,475 --> 00:42:25,615
Do you like strawberry cake?

582
00:42:26,315 --> 00:42:27,315
Mango cake?

583
00:42:27,445 --> 00:42:28,485
Yes.

584
00:42:30,085 --> 00:42:31,315
Strawberry? Mango?

585
00:42:31,985 --> 00:42:32,985
Both.

586
00:42:35,195 --> 00:42:36,195
Look at me.

587
00:42:40,395 --> 00:42:42,335
I know what you're upset about.

588
00:42:43,935 --> 00:42:44,935
But don't get me wrong.

589
00:42:45,265 --> 00:42:46,365
That goes for you.

590
00:42:47,305 --> 00:42:48,375
I'm the one getting it wrong?

591
00:42:49,475 --> 00:42:51,745
I just don't like Shine Muscat cake.

592
00:42:52,575 --> 00:42:54,045
But you added, "Don't worry."

593
00:42:55,045 --> 00:42:56,045
I don't know.

594
00:42:57,075 --> 00:42:58,745
It's just what I said in the moment.

595
00:43:04,715 --> 00:43:07,485
Reporter Geum Ba Ra, you're difficult
when you get like this.

596
00:43:09,355 --> 00:43:10,825
You're clearly in a bad mood.

597
00:43:11,725 --> 00:43:14,295
It's so obvious,
but you just keep saying you're fine.

598
00:43:15,535 --> 00:43:17,135
Am I supposed to be smiling all the time?

599
00:43:18,095 --> 00:43:20,435
I wasn't saying
you couldn't have any cake.

600
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,475
I just meant we should all share it.

601
00:43:25,675 --> 00:43:26,675
I know.

602
00:43:33,745 --> 00:43:36,285
Don't look.
You had a taste. That's enough.

603
00:43:39,055 --> 00:43:40,955
I feel like you treat Pickles better
than you treat me.

604
00:43:42,495 --> 00:43:43,895
How could you say that?

605
00:43:49,265 --> 00:43:52,035
Just be straight with me.
Tell me what's going on.

606
00:43:56,575 --> 00:43:57,675
Momo hates flowers.

607
00:43:57,935 --> 00:43:59,375
I'm the one who bought her
the pregnancy test.

608
00:43:59,875 --> 00:44:02,545
You were so excited to see Momo,
with no idea she was pregnant,

609
00:44:02,615 --> 00:44:05,145
that you brought her flowers and a cake,
which you never do for anyone.

610
00:44:07,545 --> 00:44:09,085
I just felt a little bad for her,
that's all.

611
00:44:12,485 --> 00:44:13,485
That's it?

612
00:44:19,725 --> 00:44:21,665
Once you see her living happily
with Ju Shin,

613
00:44:22,895 --> 00:44:25,565
you'll be able to let go and feel at ease.

614
00:44:27,405 --> 00:44:30,035
I'll admit, I was a little surprised.
I never saw it coming.

615
00:44:31,975 --> 00:44:35,545
But it's perfectly normal
for an engaged couple to have a baby.

616
00:44:44,185 --> 00:44:45,185
You big baby.

617
00:44:46,585 --> 00:44:48,255
Stop being so sulky.

618
00:44:48,855 --> 00:44:49,895
You're starting to scare me.

619
00:44:52,165 --> 00:44:53,165
There's that smile.

620
00:44:55,335 --> 00:44:58,195
When the baby's born,
what will the kid call you?

621
00:44:58,665 --> 00:45:00,435
Mister? Uncle?

622
00:45:01,365 --> 00:45:03,405
Uncle, mister, whatever.

623
00:45:05,045 --> 00:45:07,405
- Time to go.
- Can't I stay?

624
00:45:07,645 --> 00:45:09,015
I know you're not serious.

625
00:45:10,015 --> 00:45:11,115
I am serious.

626
00:45:11,745 --> 00:45:14,615
I really do want to sleep over
with Pickles.

627
00:45:15,385 --> 00:45:16,385
Be my guest.

628
00:45:16,955 --> 00:45:18,455
But you don't have a change of clothes.

629
00:45:21,325 --> 00:45:24,595
I wonder if Momo's baby
will be a boy or a girl.

630
00:45:26,425 --> 00:45:29,565
If it's a girl,
Ju Shin will probably soften up.

631
00:45:31,035 --> 00:45:33,535
He was so good to Momo in the beginning.

632
00:45:34,975 --> 00:45:37,075
Isn't that because his father passed away?

633
00:45:37,975 --> 00:45:39,605
After all, he's still in mourning.

634
00:45:40,945 --> 00:45:41,945
That could be it.

635
00:45:50,115 --> 00:45:52,025
I hold all the cards now, don't I?

636
00:45:55,155 --> 00:45:57,025
I should start keeping a change of clothes
in my car.

637
00:45:57,755 --> 00:45:59,795
People would get the wrong idea
if I kept a set for you here?

638
00:46:05,535 --> 00:46:08,435
- The doors are closing.
- The wrong idea? From who?

639
00:46:08,635 --> 00:46:10,575
Some of my reporter friends
come over sometimes.

640
00:46:11,205 --> 00:46:12,305
If they were to see them...

641
00:46:12,705 --> 00:46:14,245
And here I thought
I was your only close friend.

642
00:46:15,015 --> 00:46:17,215
Momo stops by sometimes too.

643
00:46:20,615 --> 00:46:22,455
Since when did you care
what other people think?

644
00:46:23,185 --> 00:46:25,985
You have to.
The world doesn't always go my way.

645
00:46:27,885 --> 00:46:30,225
Then I'll take the heat.
Move into my place.

646
00:46:35,465 --> 00:46:37,035
I really can't seem to make myself leave.

647
00:46:41,935 --> 00:46:42,935
Go on inside.

648
00:47:00,725 --> 00:47:02,055
Try to get some proper sleep this weekend.

649
00:47:03,955 --> 00:47:04,955
You look exhausted.

650
00:47:09,335 --> 00:47:10,335
What?

651
00:47:14,765 --> 00:47:16,705
You want me to get off? Stay?

652
00:47:19,505 --> 00:47:20,505
Hey...

653
00:47:22,215 --> 00:47:23,215
Yes?

654
00:47:23,645 --> 00:47:24,645
The thing is...

655
00:47:26,815 --> 00:47:28,085
I guess I was sulking.

656
00:47:29,515 --> 00:47:33,385
- I knew it!
- You treat Momo better than me.

657
00:47:33,685 --> 00:47:34,755
I was jealous and upset.

658
00:48:07,055 --> 00:48:09,395
It's wonderful to see you. Welcome.

659
00:48:09,695 --> 00:48:11,355
The lucky draw is over here.

660
00:48:11,965 --> 00:48:12,965
Okay.

661
00:48:13,625 --> 00:48:15,195
Hi! I'm a huge fan.

662
00:48:16,565 --> 00:48:17,565
Thank you.

663
00:48:20,365 --> 00:48:21,565
(Korea and Arnia 28th Anniversary
Cultural Exchange Festival)

664
00:48:25,745 --> 00:48:28,515
- You're so stunning today.
- Thank you for coming.

665
00:48:28,775 --> 00:48:31,575
You always radiate such beauty and energy.

666
00:48:31,945 --> 00:48:34,445
It's lit up here with your bright energy.

667
00:48:36,415 --> 00:48:39,355
It's been a while
since we last saw each other, hasn't it?

668
00:48:39,355 --> 00:48:41,925
Yes, indeed. So good to see you again.

669
00:48:41,995 --> 00:48:43,995
- Me too.
- Please come in.

670
00:48:46,465 --> 00:48:48,565
(Korea and Arnia 28th Anniversary
Cultural Exchange Festival)

671
00:48:54,965 --> 00:48:55,975
(Director Shin Ju Shin,
Nua General Hospital)

672
00:49:07,345 --> 00:49:08,345
Director Shin.

673
00:49:08,985 --> 00:49:10,115
Yes, Minister.

674
00:49:10,885 --> 00:49:12,455
I'm surprised to see you.
I know how busy you are.

675
00:49:12,855 --> 00:49:14,725
You're the ambassador's personal doctor?

676
00:49:14,725 --> 00:49:15,755
Yes.

677
00:49:16,795 --> 00:49:17,795
This is Minister Yu Jong Won.

678
00:49:19,095 --> 00:49:21,825
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- The pleasure is all mine.

679
00:49:23,465 --> 00:49:25,205
- And your wife?
- She's already inside.

680
00:49:25,905 --> 00:49:27,405
You're even more beautiful in person.

681
00:49:28,335 --> 00:49:30,535
- Thank you.
- We'll head inside after saying hello.

682
00:49:30,675 --> 00:49:31,675
Of course.

683
00:49:33,845 --> 00:49:35,445
Hello, Ba Ra.

684
00:49:37,045 --> 00:49:39,445
- How are you?
- I'm fine. Good to see you again.

685
00:49:39,445 --> 00:49:42,315
Yes, me too. I'm so happy to be in Korea.

686
00:49:49,525 --> 00:49:50,895
Doctor Shin.

687
00:49:52,165 --> 00:49:53,165
Thank you for inviting.

688
00:49:53,995 --> 00:49:54,995
This is Momo.

689
00:49:56,295 --> 00:49:57,335
It's a pleasure to meet you, sir.

690
00:49:57,665 --> 00:49:59,035
Please come in.

691
00:50:08,975 --> 00:50:10,275
- See you again.
- See you later.

692
00:50:12,585 --> 00:50:14,115
Hey!

693
00:50:15,145 --> 00:50:16,155
Momo's here.

694
00:50:17,685 --> 00:50:19,885
- Ms. Kim.
- Director!

695
00:50:20,155 --> 00:50:23,425
- Fancy seeing you here.
- You transferred to Sekyung? Yes.

696
00:50:25,965 --> 00:50:28,065
- You made it.
- Are you close with the Ambassador?

697
00:50:28,835 --> 00:50:30,965
We see each other now and then.
I've even been invited to the residence.

698
00:50:32,005 --> 00:50:33,865
- Go on in.
- Actually, I have to go.

699
00:50:34,205 --> 00:50:35,235
Why?

700
00:50:35,475 --> 00:50:37,305
I have an important meeting for a story.

701
00:50:42,515 --> 00:50:44,275
You should've taken
your English classes more seriously.

702
00:50:45,015 --> 00:50:47,315
Plenty of people can't speak English
even after four years at school.

703
00:50:48,445 --> 00:50:50,085
Get an English tutor immediately.

704
00:50:50,085 --> 00:50:51,555
You need to have some grit,

705
00:50:52,855 --> 00:50:53,855
like Ba Ra.

706
00:50:55,655 --> 00:50:56,955
Are you saying I don't have any grit?

707
00:50:57,355 --> 00:50:58,865
You both grew up in the same environment,

708
00:50:59,325 --> 00:51:00,765
but Ba Ra is fluent, isn't she?

709
00:51:04,865 --> 00:51:07,105
(NUA)

710
00:51:20,485 --> 00:51:21,485
I'm sorry.

711
00:51:22,415 --> 00:51:23,715
Can you just write anywhere?

712
00:51:24,085 --> 00:51:26,725
You can perform surgery anywhere
as long as you have your tools, right?

713
00:51:26,885 --> 00:51:28,255
That's only possible
because it's physical work.

714
00:51:31,355 --> 00:51:33,825
I have a hard time
just writing a birthday card.

715
00:51:35,195 --> 00:51:37,395
And I'd be terrified
just holding a scalpel.

716
00:51:46,275 --> 00:51:49,775
(Nua Children's Home)

717
00:51:59,255 --> 00:52:00,255
(Infants and Toddlers)

718
00:52:18,175 --> 00:52:19,175
(Ju Shin)

719
00:52:26,815 --> 00:52:28,185
Breathe.

720
00:52:29,385 --> 00:52:30,515
And rotate.

721
00:52:31,985 --> 00:52:34,785
Keep your shoulders still.
Now, deep breath in.

722
00:52:34,855 --> 00:52:36,195
- Almost there.
- Okay.

723
00:52:36,455 --> 00:52:38,055
There you go.

724
00:52:38,625 --> 00:52:40,825
Okay, that's it.

725
00:52:43,165 --> 00:52:45,065
We've decided to grant you
a one-year leave of absence,

726
00:52:45,405 --> 00:52:47,305
so take that time to think things over
and then decide.

727
00:52:51,935 --> 00:52:52,945
Okay.

728
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:54,805
How about we get married
at the vacation house?

729
00:52:57,315 --> 00:52:58,315
There are no wedding venues available.

730
00:52:59,345 --> 00:53:01,315
The high-end hotels are fully booked
until the end of next year.

731
00:53:02,955 --> 00:53:04,255
I don't want an outdoor wedding.

732
00:53:05,425 --> 00:53:07,125
I don't care if we wait.
I want it to be at the Sera Hotel.

733
00:53:07,725 --> 00:53:08,755
Does it have to be the Sera Hotel?

734
00:53:08,955 --> 00:53:10,325
They say the photos are great there.

735
00:53:11,755 --> 00:53:12,825
After the baby's born?

736
00:53:13,325 --> 00:53:14,425
I lost...

737
00:53:14,825 --> 00:53:15,895
the baby.

738
00:53:17,495 --> 00:53:18,495
What do you mean you lost it?

739
00:53:19,565 --> 00:53:20,565
I had a miscarriage.

740
00:53:26,445 --> 00:53:27,445
When?

741
00:53:30,845 --> 00:53:31,845
Why didn't you tell me?

742
00:53:32,815 --> 00:53:35,915
You have surgery every single day.
I was afraid it would throw you off.

743
00:53:36,785 --> 00:53:37,815
Besides, it's not exactly good news.

744
00:53:40,155 --> 00:53:41,355
We can always try again.

745
00:53:45,195 --> 00:53:46,195
Which hospital?

746
00:53:48,425 --> 00:53:49,495
Why didn't you come to me?

747
00:53:51,535 --> 00:53:52,535
Why didn't you tell me?

748
00:54:04,915 --> 00:54:07,415
How dare you lie to me?

749
00:54:08,315 --> 00:54:09,315
Lie?

750
00:54:10,355 --> 00:54:11,385
Why would I?

751
00:54:12,115 --> 00:54:14,425
Then name the hospital. Why can't you?

752
00:54:14,485 --> 00:54:17,755
If you can't trust me, how can we marry?

753
00:54:17,755 --> 00:54:18,825
That's my point.

754
00:54:20,365 --> 00:54:21,795
You have to act trustworthy
if you want to be trusted.

755
00:54:23,165 --> 00:54:26,205
Director Park Sun Jung.
You know her, right?

756
00:54:27,465 --> 00:54:29,205
She promised she'd keep it confidential.

757
00:54:34,075 --> 00:54:35,075
Is this who you really are?

758
00:54:36,045 --> 00:54:37,275
Do you think I'm a pushover and a joke?

759
00:54:37,915 --> 00:54:39,645
I have dignity, you know.

760
00:54:39,715 --> 00:54:41,515
Then you should've just told me
the truth from the start.

761
00:54:42,285 --> 00:54:43,785
How can you enjoy strawberries right now?

762
00:54:44,485 --> 00:54:45,485
Like nothing's wrong?

763
00:54:45,555 --> 00:54:49,025
Yes. I must be low on Vitamin C
because they're delicious.

764
00:54:50,355 --> 00:54:51,455
This is really pissing me off.

765
00:54:53,825 --> 00:54:54,825
You're pissed off?

766
00:54:55,595 --> 00:54:56,665
Would I feel good after getting hit?

767
00:54:57,195 --> 00:54:58,265
If I did, I'd be a sicko.

768
00:54:58,905 --> 00:55:00,135
It's not like I'm the one who's pregnant.

769
00:55:01,305 --> 00:55:03,535
You're right. I think it's for the best.

770
00:55:05,675 --> 00:55:06,745
Check for yourself.

771
00:55:10,545 --> 00:55:12,115
She said I could call her anytime.

772
00:55:13,145 --> 00:55:14,715
You should've been worried
and asked if I was okay first.

773
00:55:18,455 --> 00:55:22,025
Don't tell me you think
we cooked this up together.

774
00:55:23,695 --> 00:55:24,795
This isn't just some minor issue.

775
00:55:25,355 --> 00:55:26,865
Was this something you should have
handled by yourself?

776
00:55:26,995 --> 00:55:30,665
That shows how much she thought of you.
She was worried you'd be upset.

777
00:55:31,365 --> 00:55:32,665
Are you just going to hit me
whenever you want?

778
00:55:34,105 --> 00:55:36,475
- Watch your mouth.
- And you're so classy you use violence?

779
00:55:36,535 --> 00:55:38,435
Are you going to argue
with every single thing I say?

780
00:55:46,985 --> 00:55:47,985
I'm sorry.

781
00:55:50,055 --> 00:55:51,915
Then act like someone
I can continue to respect.

782
00:55:53,085 --> 00:55:55,425
Respect is earned through
courtesy and consideration.

783
00:55:56,395 --> 00:55:58,055
I'm the only son in my family.
You don't think this kills me?

784
00:55:58,495 --> 00:56:00,995
- It's not like you control having kids.
- That's my point.

785
00:56:05,395 --> 00:56:06,665
I told you not to swim.

786
00:56:09,935 --> 00:56:11,375
Do you have any idea
how strenuous swimming is?

787
00:56:12,505 --> 00:56:15,105
- And that's why you miscarried.
- It was fate.

788
00:56:15,645 --> 00:56:17,615
- A proper marriage...
- Fate? What nonsense is that?

789
00:56:18,945 --> 00:56:21,615
You should've been careful. It was early.

790
00:56:21,745 --> 00:56:22,985
I was trying to have a healthy baby.

791
00:56:23,055 --> 00:56:24,055
Don't make excuses.

792
00:56:24,915 --> 00:56:26,485
You took those swimming lessons
on purpose.

793
00:56:28,755 --> 00:56:29,925
I'm sick with pent-up rage, you know.

794
00:56:32,365 --> 00:56:34,625
You tell me to be Momo, but you treat me
like the old Kim Jin Ju.

795
00:56:36,335 --> 00:56:37,765
This is the last time
I'm letting this slide.

796
00:56:46,775 --> 00:56:47,845
Stop trying to be clever.

797
00:56:49,275 --> 00:56:50,315
Stop your petty little schemes.

798
00:57:15,705 --> 00:57:17,735
I'm the one in control now.

799
00:57:26,285 --> 00:57:27,285
Yong Joong.

800
00:57:29,285 --> 00:57:30,485
Are you avoiding me?

801
00:57:32,785 --> 00:57:33,785
Was what I said...

802
00:57:35,585 --> 00:57:37,225
too much for you?

803
00:57:47,035 --> 00:57:49,475
- Hello.
- I'm sorry, he's not in.

804
00:57:50,475 --> 00:57:53,375
- Is he running late?
- He's out of the country.

805
00:57:54,305 --> 00:57:57,015
- What about Pickles?
- James took him.

806
00:58:20,405 --> 00:58:21,405
Meow.

807
00:58:25,075 --> 00:58:26,175
Meow.

808
00:58:27,105 --> 00:58:28,105
Yong Joong.

809
00:58:31,715 --> 00:58:32,715
There's a little kitten.

810
00:58:34,945 --> 00:58:37,315
- How big?
- About 20cm?

811
00:58:37,955 --> 00:58:39,055
It's skin and bones.

812
00:58:51,635 --> 00:58:53,705
Did I really have to hear it
from your housekeeper...

813
00:58:53,705 --> 00:58:54,835
that you went abroad?

814
00:58:55,975 --> 00:58:57,205
Abroad?

815
00:58:57,205 --> 00:58:59,105
It was just a business trip
to a nearby country for a few days.

816
00:59:04,045 --> 00:59:05,045
You went to my place?

817
00:59:05,915 --> 00:59:07,045
Because you missed me?

818
00:59:08,015 --> 00:59:10,585
Why didn't you call?
I could've been home late.

819
00:59:11,115 --> 00:59:13,155
I didn't want to disturb you
because you're always meeting people.

820
00:59:14,985 --> 00:59:16,955
I figured the lights would just turn on
when I you got home.

821
00:59:18,725 --> 00:59:19,995
Meow.

822
00:59:22,025 --> 00:59:23,965
You know, some cats will come
and rub right up against you.

823
00:59:25,805 --> 00:59:26,865
In other countries,

824
00:59:27,365 --> 00:59:28,565
like in Europe,

825
00:59:29,635 --> 00:59:31,275
they always keep
their garden sandboxes covered.

826
00:59:31,775 --> 00:59:33,545
It's because stray cats
will use it as a litter box.

827
00:59:34,645 --> 00:59:38,215
Ever do "Pat-a-Cake?"
Have you ever played that?

828
00:59:39,185 --> 00:59:41,485
No, but I've been buried in the sand.

829
00:59:42,145 --> 00:59:44,185
- At the beach?
- Of course. Where else?

830
00:59:45,455 --> 00:59:46,555
What's it like?

831
00:59:47,285 --> 00:59:48,285
I'm curious.

832
00:59:49,195 --> 00:59:50,395
Let's go now.

833
00:59:50,455 --> 00:59:51,495
Find out for yourself.

834
00:59:52,025 --> 00:59:53,025
How?

835
00:59:53,295 --> 00:59:54,295
Why not? We have a car.

836
00:59:55,065 --> 00:59:57,465
You must be tired.
Just go home and unpack.

837
00:59:57,535 --> 00:59:59,865
I'm not tired at all,
and I have nothing to unpack.

838
00:59:59,965 --> 01:00:01,035
All I have is my carry-on.

839
01:00:04,435 --> 01:00:05,435
Want to try driving?

840
01:00:07,545 --> 01:00:08,575
This expensive car?

841
01:00:09,005 --> 01:00:10,615
There's a rest stop coming up soon.

842
01:00:12,015 --> 01:00:13,115
No way. I'm too scared.

843
01:00:13,945 --> 01:00:15,385
"A chicken instead of a pheasant."

844
01:00:15,645 --> 01:00:16,885
Momo's the one who should be here.

845
01:00:17,655 --> 01:00:18,885
Don't say that.

846
01:00:19,525 --> 01:00:22,325
You're neither a chicken nor a pheasant.
You, Geum Ba Ra, are a peacock.

847
01:00:23,595 --> 01:00:25,525
The male peacocks are the flashy ones.

848
01:00:25,795 --> 01:00:27,725
Exactly. You're not flashy.

849
01:00:29,335 --> 01:00:31,235
You're graceful and elegant.

850
01:00:33,165 --> 01:00:34,405
You're too much.

851
01:00:36,675 --> 01:00:37,875
I'm not graceful in the slightest.

852
01:00:40,945 --> 01:00:43,015
It's not about how you're dressed,
it's your aura.

853
01:00:46,115 --> 01:00:47,285
Is Momo having trouble eating?

854
01:00:49,785 --> 01:00:50,785
Morning sickness.

855
01:00:54,055 --> 01:00:55,185
She says she doesn't want to have it.

856
01:00:56,495 --> 01:00:58,495
- The baby?
- Yes.

857
01:00:58,695 --> 01:01:01,025
- Why not?
- She says she's not ready.

858
01:01:02,735 --> 01:01:03,795
But she has to.

859
01:01:07,135 --> 01:01:09,905
I saw Momo and Director Shin
at the embassy party.

860
01:01:10,175 --> 01:01:11,805
They seemed so happy.

861
01:01:13,045 --> 01:01:14,075
Which embassy?

862
01:01:14,745 --> 01:01:15,745
Arnia.

863
01:01:18,415 --> 01:01:20,115
If you're not going to drive,
why don't you get some sleep?

864
01:01:21,045 --> 01:01:22,145
Are you sure you're not tired?

865
01:01:22,655 --> 01:01:23,655
Not tired.

866
01:01:24,055 --> 01:01:27,355
Driving on an open road like this
is actually a great way to de-stress.

867
01:01:30,995 --> 01:01:33,325
You seem like the kind of person
who never gets stressed out.

868
01:01:34,165 --> 01:01:35,825
You're right. I rarely do.

869
01:01:36,195 --> 01:01:37,335
It's just not in my nature
to get stressed.

870
01:01:38,795 --> 01:01:41,305
You have no flaws. No shortcomings.

871
01:01:43,905 --> 01:01:45,075
Just one request.

872
01:01:46,045 --> 01:01:47,075
What is it?

873
01:01:47,075 --> 01:01:49,045
Don't ever shave your head
and become a monk,

874
01:01:49,045 --> 01:01:50,115
seeking enlightenment.

875
01:01:52,115 --> 01:01:53,285
Did I figure out your secret plan?

876
01:01:53,645 --> 01:01:55,115
I've never even considered it.

877
01:01:55,745 --> 01:01:58,085
I've just read a lot of books by monks,
that's all.

878
01:01:58,685 --> 01:02:00,655
Actually, not that many. Maybe 20 or so?

879
01:02:01,785 --> 01:02:04,825
Hasn't that head monk you know so well
ever suggested it?

880
01:02:05,155 --> 01:02:07,795
Head monks don't just ask anyone
to shave their head.

881
01:02:07,995 --> 01:02:11,195
They have an eye for seeing
a person's true capacity.

882
01:02:12,035 --> 01:02:14,535
He probably saw right through
my materialistic nature.

883
01:02:15,905 --> 01:02:17,235
You? Materialistic?

884
01:02:22,405 --> 01:02:23,845
I've thought about it, though.

885
01:02:24,545 --> 01:02:25,815
About becoming a nun.

886
01:02:26,815 --> 01:02:27,945
Why?

887
01:02:27,945 --> 01:02:30,115
Kids who used to bully me in school
would say...

888
01:02:31,385 --> 01:02:33,225
"Ashes, ashes, Ba Ra falls down."

889
01:02:34,125 --> 01:02:35,655
They used to tease me with that sometimes.

890
01:02:37,055 --> 01:02:38,695
I could have been born in a temple,
you know?

891
01:02:40,865 --> 01:02:41,865
No, you weren't.

892
01:02:43,365 --> 01:02:45,565
My eyes are stinging a little.
I'm just going to close them for a bit.

893
01:02:45,965 --> 01:02:47,065
Alright.

894
01:02:49,605 --> 01:02:50,605
Should I skip the rest stop?

895
01:02:52,035 --> 01:02:54,175
You have to pull the bottle away
every so often...

896
01:02:54,745 --> 01:02:57,115
and let them take a break
for a few seconds.

897
01:02:57,545 --> 01:02:59,415
Otherwise,
since they don't know any better,

898
01:02:59,785 --> 01:03:01,945
they will just guzzle it and spit it up.

899
01:03:02,285 --> 01:03:04,155
We know how exhausting it is to throw up.

900
01:03:05,455 --> 01:03:06,485
Is this who you really are?

901
01:03:06,885 --> 01:03:08,225
Do you think I'm a pushover and a joke?

902
01:03:08,225 --> 01:03:10,225
I have dignity, you know.

903
01:03:13,525 --> 01:03:16,065
(Aren't you going up?)

904
01:03:16,465 --> 01:03:19,135
(Are you going to do your rounds?)

905
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:32,745
How long has it been
since you've been to the beach?

906
01:03:35,515 --> 01:03:37,615
The year before last for a story.

907
01:03:38,615 --> 01:03:39,625
That long ago?

908
01:03:40,725 --> 01:03:41,725
What about you?

909
01:03:42,485 --> 01:03:43,495
Last month.

910
01:03:43,995 --> 01:03:46,765
I just come here on a whim
whenever I have something on my mind.

911
01:03:48,695 --> 01:03:52,235
I guess he didn't need to come here
just to think about what I said.

912
01:03:57,675 --> 01:03:59,235
I think they maintain the sand here.

913
01:03:59,545 --> 01:04:01,875
It's always clean.
There aren't even any seashells.

914
01:04:13,655 --> 01:04:15,025
Speaking of regrets,

915
01:04:15,985 --> 01:04:16,995
I do have one.

916
01:04:19,055 --> 01:04:20,095
My dad and I...

917
01:04:20,795 --> 01:04:22,765
never got to play catch. Not even once.

918
01:04:25,165 --> 01:04:26,365
He was always so busy.

919
01:04:29,365 --> 01:04:31,105
Doing it at a beach like this...

920
01:04:31,975 --> 01:04:33,145
would've been so nice.

921
01:04:36,545 --> 01:04:39,915
Nine is too young to lose your father.

922
01:04:40,785 --> 01:04:41,785
Tell me about it.

923
01:04:45,915 --> 01:04:48,655
So I can't even imagine
what it's like for you.

924
01:04:56,065 --> 01:04:58,365
When you look at those waves
endlessly crashing on the shore,

925
01:04:59,095 --> 01:05:00,165
what comes to mind?

926
01:05:03,705 --> 01:05:05,205
Right now, nothing.

927
01:05:07,405 --> 01:05:09,715
It just feels refreshing to watch them.

928
01:05:10,615 --> 01:05:11,715
Does it help you feel a little lighter?

929
01:05:15,615 --> 01:05:17,355
What about you? What comes to mind?

930
01:05:20,025 --> 01:05:22,325
They remind me of the adversities
we face in life.

931
01:05:24,325 --> 01:05:27,095
You get over one hurdle,
and there's another.

932
01:05:28,765 --> 01:05:31,395
I suppose my waves have been
relatively calm,

933
01:05:31,665 --> 01:05:32,665
so far, at least.

934
01:05:36,135 --> 01:05:39,175
But you, Ba Ra, from a very early age...

935
01:05:40,075 --> 01:05:42,045
were hit by a tidal wave,

936
01:05:43,515 --> 01:05:45,045
but you weren't swept away. You held on.

937
01:05:47,015 --> 01:05:48,085
I'm so incredibly proud of you.

938
01:05:52,855 --> 01:05:53,855
When I was in Japan,

939
01:05:56,085 --> 01:05:57,595
I thought long and hard
about what you said...

940
01:05:59,295 --> 01:06:00,495
Where is my head?

941
01:06:00,495 --> 01:06:01,795
What's wrong with me?

942
01:06:01,795 --> 01:06:03,635
- What is it?
- It's in the car!

943
01:06:12,175 --> 01:06:14,005
- For today...
- You don't need to show us.

944
01:06:14,345 --> 01:06:15,345
All right.

945
01:06:17,675 --> 01:06:19,075
How are you so good with babies?

946
01:06:19,585 --> 01:06:21,215
Try asking what I'm not good at.

947
01:07:02,185 --> 01:07:03,455
I left it in the trunk.

948
01:07:07,125 --> 01:07:08,495
You brought this just for me?

949
01:07:08,895 --> 01:07:09,895
Of course. Who else?

950
01:07:17,475 --> 01:07:20,175
- You probably can't smell it by the sea.
- I can.

951
01:07:20,645 --> 01:07:23,175
That explains it. On the drive here,
I wondered if you bought a perfume.

952
01:07:24,175 --> 01:07:25,975
I didn't get you any
because I didn't think you wore perfume.

953
01:07:26,485 --> 01:07:28,145
That's because I don't have any to wear.

954
01:07:28,745 --> 01:07:29,815
I'll buy you some first thing tomorrow.

955
01:07:30,115 --> 01:07:31,915
I'm just kidding. I don't wear any.

956
01:07:33,185 --> 01:07:34,555
I hope the cream didn't melt.

957
01:07:34,885 --> 01:07:37,455
It should be fine.
Look, they put an ice pack in.

958
01:07:45,965 --> 01:07:47,405
I'm sorry it took me this long
to give you flowers.

959
01:07:48,605 --> 01:07:50,135
I should have given them to you first.

960
01:07:50,905 --> 01:07:54,375
It's not like big brothers usually do this
for their little sisters, anyway.

961
01:07:57,275 --> 01:07:59,175
Even now, that first time we met
in front of the supermarket...

962
01:08:00,545 --> 01:08:01,945
feels like only yesterday.

963
01:08:01,945 --> 01:08:03,515
Your eyes were just filled with tears.

964
01:08:05,055 --> 01:08:07,725
Just forget it.
It's not exactly a good memory.

965
01:08:08,585 --> 01:08:10,195
It's not about whether
it's a good or bad memory.

966
01:08:12,225 --> 01:08:13,965
When I think about
what you said back then,

967
01:08:15,165 --> 01:08:16,435
my heart just aches.

968
01:08:18,695 --> 01:08:20,665
I realize I never truly understood
what you were going through.

969
01:08:21,235 --> 01:08:22,635
And I'm supposed to be
the one closest to you.

970
01:08:28,175 --> 01:08:29,175
Aren't I?

971
01:08:30,715 --> 01:08:31,715
You are.

972
01:08:32,715 --> 01:08:33,985
It wasn't that I was being insensitive.

973
01:08:35,345 --> 01:08:36,755
It was just that instead of
a small gift like a cake,

974
01:08:37,415 --> 01:08:39,785
I wanted to do something
so much better for you.

975
01:08:47,425 --> 01:08:48,495
To me...

976
01:08:51,095 --> 01:08:52,535
you're not a little kid anymore.

977
01:08:55,065 --> 01:08:56,335
And at some point,

978
01:08:58,475 --> 01:09:00,205
I started to see you in a different light.

979
01:09:56,795 --> 01:09:59,695
(Doctor Shin)

980
01:09:59,935 --> 01:10:01,765
- Thank you.
- Are you her stylist?

981
01:10:01,835 --> 01:10:02,835
I'm still just an assistant.

982
01:10:02,905 --> 01:10:06,305
If Ba Ra finds out it's me and not Momo,
she is going to flip out.

983
01:10:06,375 --> 01:10:09,275
Since you've decided,
can't you just do it once?

984
01:10:09,345 --> 01:10:10,415
If you come with me,

985
01:10:11,215 --> 01:10:12,345
I'll go three times instead of twice.

986
01:10:12,875 --> 01:10:15,245
- Four times?
- I'll go with you every single time.

987
01:10:15,315 --> 01:10:17,715
He might want to get rid of me,

988
01:10:17,715 --> 01:10:19,285
but he can't just take out the brain.

989
01:10:19,355 --> 01:10:21,255
To get rid of me, he'd have to kill Momo.

990
01:10:21,255 --> 01:10:23,325
Could he kill Momo and get away with it?

991
01:10:23,455 --> 01:10:24,455
Do you like Director Shin?

992
01:10:24,725 --> 01:10:26,155
I used to have feelings for him.

993
01:10:26,295 --> 01:10:29,935
- Grandpa says she died and came back.
- From the dead?

994
01:10:29,995 --> 01:10:33,735
To Kim Jin Ju, Director Shin is
a deity or her Prince Charming.

995
01:10:33,805 --> 01:10:34,865
But now it's my turn.

996
01:10:36,135 --> 01:10:37,705
- Hey, James.
- Get over here, quick!

997
01:10:37,775 --> 01:10:39,275
- What's wrong?
- What am I going to do?

998
01:10:41,745 --> 01:10:42,845
My first love is...

999
01:10:43,105 --> 01:10:44,315
Ba Ra.

1000
01:10:47,315 --> 01:10:49,315
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
